SIMPLE: squall
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Squall
<hw>Squall</hw> <pr>(skw⟦add⟧l)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. Sw.
<ets>sqval</ets> an impetuous running of water, <ets>sqval</ets>regn a
violent shower of rain, <ets>sqvala</ets> to stream, to gush.]</ety>
<def>A sudden and violent gust of wind often attended with rain or
snow.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The gray skirts of a lifting <qex>squall</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Tennyson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Black squall</b></col>, <cd>a squall attended with dark,
heavy clouds.</cd> -- <col><b>Thick squall</b></col>, <cd>a black squall
accompanied by rain, hail, sleet, or snow.</cd> <au>Totten.</au> --
<col><b>White squall</b></col>, <cd>a squall which comes unexpectedly,
without being marked in its approach by the clouds.</cd>
<rj><au>Totten.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Squall</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Squall
<hw>Squall</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Squalled</conjf> <pr>(skw⟦add⟧ld)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Squalling</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Icel.
<ets>skvala</ets>. Cf. <er>Squeal</er>.]</ety> <def>To cry out; to
scream or cry violently, as a woman frightened, or a child in anger or
distress; <as>as, the infant <ex>squalled</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Squall</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Squall
<hw>Squall</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A loud scream; a harsh
cry.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>There oft are heard the notes of infant woe, --⟦br⟧
The short, thick sob, loud scream, and shriller <qex>squall</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Squaller</ent>⟦br⟧
